commit_message:
Adds model mixin for {to,from}_dict functionality

Implements ModelDictMixin, which is an alternative to DictBase that does
not force a module to have an "extra" field. It also gets away from the
idea that we need to keep a list of attibutes, named `attributes`, on
each model definition.

Change-Id: Id2c208ee9be4cc17b1b6444c5e0558952571163b
Fixes-bug: #1265071

commit_message:
feat(v1.1): Plumb v1.1 API in the WSGI transport

This patch creates a copy of the v1.0 API as a starting point for
implementing the v1.1 API. The way that the "admin_mode" config option was
implemented was changed, in order to simplify the grafting of the two API
versions into a single driver. When the mode was implemented via inheritance,
grafting the two API versions required some ugly hacks.

Partially-Implements: blueprint api-v1.1
Change-Id: I0e753315e3171bb5c23a57b8fb3826d08bfd5f26

commit_message:
clean up security groups tests

This patch clean up test codes of security groups in the
following items:
1. add a helper function create_new_security_group to replace the
   duplicate codes in test methods
2. remove duplicate test case test_security_group_create_delete
   in test_security_groups.py
3. use data_utils.rand_uuid() instead of str(uuid.uuid4())
4. import test module instead of attr

Change-Id: Iaf1a267134a12a664a0f306980c9cb39fe5ac1eb

commit_message:
Fix usage of dict.keys in apiclient.exceptions

Method dict.keys returns a dict_keys object in Python 3, which is
not indexable, so we get exception TypeError ('dict_keys' object does not
support indexing). This is fix of usage dict object in module exceptions.

Related to bp make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: Ie827f408cd23d4baa900f2ae1b074d13a5cd6f0e

commit_message:
Fix syntax error in controller node sql setup

The mysql shell command has redundant prompt which leads to incorrect
sql command, this patch simply removes the unnecessary characters.

Note, this patch also adds a single space after each prompt character
'>', this is same to the real mysql shell environment.

Change-Id: I3980d79dee88dcdf7add541bda59d97bf670be01
Closes-Bug: #1282039

revisions:

The documentation asks the user to use openstack-config to apply
a change to the root_helper parameter. With the way that
openstack-config works it expects parameters to be organised properly.
Therefore, any white space between arguments is assumed to be

commit_message:
Fixes root_helper copy and paste problem with openstack-config

The documentation asks the user to use openstack-config to apply
a change to the root_helper parameter. With the way that
openstack-config works it expects parameters to be organised properly.
Therefore, any white space between arguments is assumed to be
a seperate argument, hence it is ignored; the solution is to
parenthesise the parameter required, encompassing all white space.

Note: Rebased since https://review.openstack.org/#/c/74243/

Change-Id: I2ab702d97828311f3fa409b6cb88931cd5f6c315
Closes-Bug: #1281565
backport: havana

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-05 17:29:47.000000000', 'files': ['reference/incubation-integration-requirements'], 'message': "Add a requirement for deprecating duplicated code

This patch updates graduation requirements related to scope.  The requirements
currently say a project must not duplicate the scope of another project.
However, we have some cases where a project intentionally duplicates
functionality with the intent of replacing it (Neutron, Cinder).

In that case, I believe we should have an additional requirement that the new
project may not graduate until it has reached a level of functionality and
maturity where we're able to deprecate the component it is replacing with a
known timeline for removal.

Change-Id: I5305e2f80ebc3c78ef74b0957337fe11c3f3de08
"}]
commit_message:
Add a requirement for deprecating duplicated code

This patch updates graduation requirements related to scope.  The requirements
currently say a project must not duplicate the scope of another project.
However, we have some cases where a project intentionally duplicates
functionality with the intent of replacing it (Neutron, Cinder).

In that case, I believe we should have an additional requirement that the new
project may not graduate until it has reached a level of functionality and
maturity where we're able to deprecate the component it is replacing with a
known timeline for removal.

Change-Id: I5305e2f80ebc3c78ef74b0957337fe11c3f3de08

in tests for ceph

As oslo.messaging 1.3.0.a7 was released, there was change

commit_message:
Fix issue with new oslo.messaging

As oslo.messaging 1.3.0.a7 was released, there was change
https://review.openstack.org/62931 merged to it. It caused
intersection issue between openstack.common.service.Service
and oslo.messaging.MessageHandlingServer classes both used
in Climate (no periodic tasks running as symptom here).

This change fixes that, working both with oslo.messaging 1.3.0.a7
and previous versions.

Change-Id: Icb7d88d4a0cb1ed568b731ca9716982eb8ffb092
Closes-Bug: #1281521

commit_message:
Initial devstack support implemented

* Install climate, climate-nova and climate client
* Sets all needed climate configs, even the nova ones in order to use
climate-nova
* Starts/Stops climate-api and climate-manager
* Creates the Keystone V3 service/endpoint if don't exists.

Change-Id: I7c5014fc61238206ea589b01f3ec0ecac005d846
Implements: blueprint climate-devstack-gating
Co-Authored-By: Pablo Andres Fuente <pablo.a.fuente@intel.com>

commit_message:
Cleanup node['cpu']['total'] work-around for fauxhai

The fauxhai fix for the cpu stanza has merged and is available in
fauxhai version 2.1.0 so reverting the workaround patch and ensuring
fauxhai 2.1.0 is used.

- Remove the node.set for ['cpu']['total']
- Adjust the Gemfile to use fauxhai 2.1.0
- Adjust the Gemfile.lock

Change-Id: Ib1fc86af1306d5443721400589a8c830263c0767
Addresses: blueprint fauxhai-cleanup

commit_message:
Adds clarity to the usage of the authorisation token

As reported in LP#1277289, the usage of the authorisation
token is not clear in the instructions. It refers to a token
previously created but potentially leaves the user
confused as to which one to use. This patch adds the clarity
required and posts a link to the documentation section.

Change-Id: Ib16bd2770d4c4aac5292e9a3d2f25c2417e818f2
Closes-Bug: #1277289
backport: havana

revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2014-02-18 21:04:04.000000000', 'files': ['elements/os-svc-install/bin/os-svc-daemon', 'elements/os-svc-install/bin/os-svc-enable'], 'message': "Ability to add *-create-dir service separately

For systemd services, we create 2 services: one for the daemon and one
that creates the run directory under /var/run for the daemon.

For the packaged installs, the daemon service is already provided by the
package, so we need the ability to add just the *-create-dir service.

Some might say that the package should create it's run directory...and

/var/run and the package uses /var/lib. Since /var/run is tmpfs mounted,
we need the *-create-dir services for the packages as well.

Change-Id: If26d9d7da04d3d1d97809db0e21e54dd9f8042ca
"}]
commit_message:
Ability to add *-create-dir service separately

For systemd services, we create 2 services: one for the daemon and one
that creates the run directory under /var/run for the daemon.

For the packaged installs, the daemon service is already provided by the
package, so we need the ability to add just the *-create-dir service.

Some might say that the package should create it's run directory...and
it in fact does. However, we are reconfiguring the services to use
/var/run and the package uses /var/lib. Since /var/run is tmpfs mounted,
we need the *-create-dir services for the packages as well.

Change-Id: If26d9d7da04d3d1d97809db0e21e54dd9f8042ca

subject: Removed specific version in development docs
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-18 18:52:47.000000000', 'files': ['docs/conf.py'], 'message': "Removed specific version in development docs

I suggest to remove the version number completely
for the following reasons:
1. Fuel version is tracked in the other repository
   at the moment (fuel-main), so every release would
   require modifications of conf.py file (which
   we we actually doing before), so can always be in
   a situation of 'outdated' development docs
2. It looks like there is no reason to handle versions
   of development documentation, which always must
   reflect the current state of master. Basically,
   saying that it is 4.0 in the middle of 4.1 release
   is wrong.

Closes-Bug: #1263642

Change-Id: Iac3f7afdf2a4bd1949d1d36444d32413ff5d169d
"}]
commit_message:
Removed specific version in development docs

I suggest to remove the version number completely
for the following reasons:
1. Fuel version is tracked in the other repository
   at the moment (fuel-main), so every release would
   require modifications of conf.py file (which
   we we actually doing before), so can always be in
   a situation of 'outdated' development docs
2. It looks like there is no reason to handle versions
   of development documentation, which always must
   reflect the current state of master. Basically,
   saying that it is 4.0 in the middle of 4.1 release
   is wrong.

Closes-Bug: #1263642

Change-Id: Iac3f7afdf2a4bd1949d1d36444d32413ff5d169d

Create volume dropdown not showing auto-generated name

When launching instances that create new volumes, the display
name is not set, and only the volume size is present on volume
creation form.
If display_name is not present, then show the id.

commit_message:
Adds to Keystone to convert V2 endpoints to V3

The Domain Quota Management Driver uses the V3 Authentication Token.
Also, it tries to contact Keystone for getting list of projects in a
domain using V3 API like /v3/projects?domain_id=<id>. But the
keystone v3/client.py default uses V2 API and hence code changed
to convert V2 endpoints for V3 endpoints. This change is required
to implement blue print domain-quota-driver-api

Change-Id: I4b2326151f6f08fea8b9ace97cc756797bf4c59f

commit_message:
Adds Keystone V3 API Calling Support

The Domain Quota Management only works with Keystone V3 Authentication.
Also, in it there is a need for Nova to contact Keystone for getting list of
projects in a domain. But even though Nova asks the Keystone to use the V3,
the Keystone v3/client.py default uses V2. So, code changed to use V3.

Change-Id: I39ac49f95912e56558a6cd2650fe0c8904884f25

commit_message:
Adds to Keystone to convert V2 endpoints to V3

The Domain Quota Management Driver uses the V3 Authentication Token.
Also, it tries to contact Keystone for getting list of projects in a
domain using V3 API like /v3/projects?domain_id=<id>. But the
keystone v3/client.py default uses V2 API and hence code changed
to convert V2 endpoints for V3 endpoints. This change is required
to implement blue print domain-quota-driver-api

commit_message:
Check all networks assignment in NICsHandler

When a network assignment is updated by NodeNICsHandler or NodeCollectionNICsHandler
all cluster networks must be assigned to the node. It didn't check the 'fuelweb_admin'
network before.
Two tests added.

Closes-bug: 1272315

commit_message:
Add common code to matchers

Several projects use the same matchers for dicts and XML files,
leading to code duplication. So far, this is included in
nova, keystone, ironic and trove projects.

This is the nova matchers file pep8 clean. Other projects matchers,
are just a copy (with minimal divergences) or a subset of this one.

Change-Id: Id2d74a6eaf9aa295165b7f78586581e661beb91f
Partial-Bug: #1199536

commit_message:
Move API invocation code in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the classes in
VMware drivers for session and API call management calls into OSLO.

The api module in this change contains classes to invoke VIM APIs.
It supports automatic session re-establishment and retry of API
invocations in case of connection problems or server API call overload.

Change-Id: Ica2eb81af5aed0fd47bd23c16dea9eca3bf56031
Implements: blueprint vmware-api

for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new

planning to use this common code. This change moves the classes defining
read and write handles for image transfer between VMware servers and
image service into OSLO.

commit_message:
Move utility methods in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the utility methods
for inventory traversal spec creation, managed object property retrieval
etc. defined in various drivers into OSLO.

Change-Id: I7cb79186028e405462b92a6ba2e37298d5ca0f9b
Implements: blueprint vmware-api

subject: PCI reqeust support pci-flavor specs
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-01-03 08:32:38.000000000', 'files': ['nova/pci/pci_request.py', 'nova/tests/pci/test_pci_request.py'], 'message': "PCI reqeust support pci-flavor specs

The pci_passthrough:pci-flavor scope in flavor extra_specs
describes the pci-flavor name, the key is 'pci_passthrough:pci-flavor'
and the value has format:
  'count1:<pci-flavor-name1>, <name2>; count2:<pci-flavor-name2>'.

The flavor's requirement in instance type extra_specs is translated
to pci requests list used to schedule and allocation device.

requests spec compare to the pci_stats, all infomation in the stats
is flat dict, all (k,v) pair is treated as basic spec.

bp:pci-extra-info

Change-Id: I50de411a6b7519f4ea309cb56fab9c8f11807ffe
"}]
commit_message:
PCI reqeust support pci-flavor specs

The pci_passthrough:pci-flavor scope in flavor extra_specs
describes the pci-flavor name, the key is 'pci_passthrough:pci-flavor'
and the value has format:
  'count1:<pci-flavor-name1>, <name2>; count2:<pci-flavor-name2>'.

The flavor's requirement in instance type extra_specs is translated
to pci requests list used to schedule and allocation device.

requests spec compare to the pci_stats, all infomation in the stats
is flat dict, all (k,v) pair is treated as basic spec.

bp:pci-extra-info

Sined-off-by: Yongli He <yongli.he@intel.com>

Change-Id: I50de411a6b7519f4ea309cb56fab9c8f11807ffe

and from rest client itself.

subject: Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-13 15:05:21.000000000', 'files': ['heat/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py'], 'message': "Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

cherry pick, including original commit message below from
oslo-incubator commit:

b4f72b2987d53bb434e3a833f06d70a2167f5efc

Closes bug: 1275838

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

(cherry picked from commit 472c1440677440e0888570926b49542ddf260724)

Conflicts:
	heat/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py

Change-Id: Id8a1c0665468b503b092c4f01ffd40e2be9c6fa9
"}]
commit_message:
Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

cherry pick, including original commit message below from
oslo-incubator commit:

b4f72b2987d53bb434e3a833f06d70a2167f5efc

Closes bug: 1275838

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

(cherry picked from commit 472c1440677440e0888570926b49542ddf260724)

Conflicts:
	heat/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py

Change-Id: Id8a1c0665468b503b092c4f01ffd40e2be9c6fa9

Restructure KDS options to be more like Keystone's options

Restructure the KDS options to be more closely aligned with the way
Keystone options work and allowing movement towards not registering
the options on import. This will also prevent KDS options from

[{'number': 11, 'created': '2014-02-17 15:06:37.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/resources/__init__.py'], 'message': "Refactor resource loading functions

All logic related to resource loading is currently put into
resource_mapping functions in each resource module and it doesn't
return the mapping information if the dependencies for a given
resources are not satisfied.

This refactors the way resources are loaded, so that the mapping
information is always available and if the dependencies are not met,
another function can be used to convey that information to heat:

commit_message:
Refactor resource loading functions

All logic related to resource loading is currently put into
resource_mapping functions in each resource module and it doesn't
return the mapping information if the dependencies for a given
resources are not satisfied.

This refactors the way resources are loaded, so that the mapping
information is always available and if the dependencies are not met,
another function can be used to convey that information to heat:
available_resource_mapping().  To keep backwards compatibility, if
available_resource_mapping() is not callable for a given resource
module, the previous resource_mapping() will be used instead.

This allows the mapping information to be used in other places, such
as tests (without the need to hard code the mapping information when
registering the resource for the tests) or doc generation (to allow
the resources to be loaded even without their dependencies).

Related-Bug: #1271226
Change-Id: Iabd3da70f7ba35e0b43a2409e170be7f41a351a6

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

subject: Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-05 21:52:55.000000000', 'files': ['heat/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py'], 'message': "Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

Closes-bug: #1276510

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

cherry pick, including original commit message from oslo-incubator commit:
b4f72b2987d53bb434e3a833f06d70a2167f5efc

Change-Id: I1fe0752d057789a944e416428f9c35c51c9f7d34
"}]
commit_message:
Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

Closes-bug: #1276510

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

cherry pick, including original commit message from oslo-incubator commit:
b4f72b2987d53bb434e3a833f06d70a2167f5efc

Change-Id: I1fe0752d057789a944e416428f9c35c51c9f7d34

commit_message:
Update Available Resources From Driver Stats

Enable the resource tracker to report available resources
from stats reported by the driver and not the audit process.
This functionality can be enabled by setting the nova.conf
variable; override_resource_audit to True.

Implement bp: use-driver-usage-stats
DocImpact: Added a new variable to nova.conf

Change-Id: Ia5ba3ea1180b209415d338b7b0ca6e21b0002b94

commit_message:
Use the next built-in instead of next method

Starting in Python 2.6, `next` became a built-in function as a backport
from Python 3. This change switches several uses of the old `next()`
method on iterables, favoring the built-in function usage.

Change-Id: Ica0452eb90f1841be8678fa13cd9ebd8e4a4d8ff

subject: python3: Fix import compatibility.
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2013-07-18 18:53:01.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'tests/test_swiftclient.py', 'tests/utils.py', 'swiftclient/client.py', 'swiftclient/https_connection.py'], 'message': 'python3: Fix import compatibility.

Python3 reorganized the standard library and moved several functions
to different modules. Six provides a consistent interface
to them through the fake six.moves module.

However, the urllib, httplib, and etc modules have been combined
into one module which Six does not support so do it the old

Change-Id: I366b198ff007a0c1b1aa52b41a95fa14a42a1153
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chuck.short@canonical.com>
'}]
commit_message:
python3: Fix import compatibility.

Python3 reorganized the standard library and moved several functions
to different modules. Six provides a consistent interface
to them through the fake six.moves module.

However, the urllib, httplib, and etc modules have been combined
into one module which Six does not support so do it the old
fashioned way.

Change-Id: I366b198ff007a0c1b1aa52b41a95fa14a42a1153
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chuck.short@canonical.com>

commit_message:
Drop nose, switching to testtools and testr

OpenStack as a whole is either in the process of, or currently making
use of testrepository and testtools as its base test infrastructure, and
so to that end bring Swift into line by switching away from nose to
testrepository. This drops nose from the test requirements, and switches
those that were making use of its imports to testtools.

Partial-Bug: 1179009
DocImpact: SAIO instructions now reference different packages to
install.

Change-Id: Ie4e17fded443a7ca1b96b9bba293f110418c2fc5

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2013-07-30 00:10:29.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'tests/utils.py', 'swiftclient/client.py'], 'message': 'python3: Add python3 compatibility support

Add python2/python3 compatibility support:

- Use six.iteritems() to replace dictionary.iteritems()

commit_message:
Six: bump to 1.5.2

In order to ensure Python 3 compatibility of the OpenStack Python clients, we
need more advanced features of six that are not included in six 1.4.1. For
instance, six.moves.xmlrpc_client only landed in six in the 1.4.2 release. Just
bump to the latest release, so that we have as many features as we can dream
of.

Change-Id: I148a9736d8271575647bfd0963771a177f8b6c1e

commit_message:
Make floating_ip_bulk_destroy deallocate quota if not auto_assigned

The expected use case for floating_ip_bulk_destroy is to destroy
auto_assigned floating IPs, for which no quota is used so no quota
needs to be recovered.  But it can also be used to destroy other
(not auto_assigned) floating IPs, in which case the previously used
quota was not recovered.  This fixes the quota leak in that unusual
case.

Closes-Bug: #1254174

Change-Id: Ibff80d9ebac8d4422e401909033da12d9ec0b593
(cherry picked from commit 384cce84fde784f9e2f39db49502c66e20ff0b4c)

This consists of the following two Patches:

    Fix a race condition in agents status update code

    Code handling agents status updates coming via RPC checks,
    if a corresponding entry for the given (agent_type, host)
    pair already exists in DB and updates it. And if it doesn't
    exist, a new entry is created.

    Without a unique constraint this can cause a race condition
    resulting in adding of two agent entries having the same value
    of (agent_type, host) pair.

    Note, that it's already not allowed to have multiple agents of
    the same type having the same host value, but currently it's
    enforced only at code level, not at DB schema level, which
    effectively makes race conditions possible.

    Fix the migration adding a UC to agents table

    The migration script mistakenly assumes that all core
    plugins use agents extension, which is not true (e.g.
    plumgrid and bigswitch don't).

    Apply this migration script only for plugins that are
    stated in the original migration script adding agents
    table (511471cc46b_agent_ext_model_supp.py).

commit_message:
Fix a race condition in agents status update code

This consists of the following two Patches:

    Fix a race condition in agents status update code

    Code handling agents status updates coming via RPC checks,
    if a corresponding entry for the given (agent_type, host)
    pair already exists in DB and updates it. And if it doesn't
    exist, a new entry is created.

    Without a unique constraint this can cause a race condition
    resulting in adding of two agent entries having the same value
    of (agent_type, host) pair.

    Note, that it's already not allowed to have multiple agents of
    the same type having the same host value, but currently it's
    enforced only at code level, not at DB schema level, which
    effectively makes race conditions possible.

    (cherry picked from commit 5529071bf1393d0d448bc495cc906a68bc30a820)

and:

    Fix the migration adding a UC to agents table

    The migration script mistakenly assumes that all core
    plugins use agents extension, which is not true (e.g.
    plumgrid and bigswitch don't).

    Apply this migration script only for plugins that are
    stated in the original migration script adding agents
    table (511471cc46b_agent_ext_model_supp.py).

    (cherry picked from commit 8b67ee3d94a4866fd4ecd27e8fc37d2f17595aa9)

Change-Id: I1ebaa111154b3d6b34074705b579097ab730594c
Closes-Bug: #1254246

commit_message:
remove duplicate ec2 request logging

because we are now using the logging handler directly in
eventlet.wsgi we current are logging twice for every ec2 request
in slightly different formats. We don't need our own log handler
on our wsgi stack, and should just use the eventlet one.

for upgrade reasons, we can't fully delete our request logger, as
it would require a paste change for the operator otherwise their
pipeline would blow up on a failed piece. So we deprecate and
stub out the request logging for Icehouse, and remove in Juno.

Implement bp: clean-logs

UpgradeImpact

Change-Id: Ifffdab98f012df5cdf1be532d1000dc7484af821

commit_message:
VPNaaS Scenario Test

Implementation of basic scenario test for VPNaaS. Sets up two
sites, creates a VPN tunnel between them, boots a server in each
site and asserts that the servers cannot ping each other before
the tunnel is created and can ping each other after the tunnel is
created.

The status attributes of the relevant service resources are also
verified to be ACTIVE after the tunnel is created.

Partially Implements: blueprint add-scenario-tests-in-icehouse

commit_message:
libvirt: alternative lxc init path

Existing default configuration for init command path is set to /sbin/init.
Users will be able to provided an alternative path, using the image properties,
to be used when starting a full os container and, as application path for a
generic application container.

glance image-update \
           --property lxc_init_path=/sbin/sh \
           [image]

DocImapct
Partially implements blueprint libvirt-lxc-application-containers
Change-Id: I0f9e9c233f077defba750a228d6f7da4a7ffcdcb

commit_message:
libvirt: Allow root directory as lxc source dir

Currently, only instance_dir/rootfs directory is being
set as the lxc source dir.
Users will be able to set the host root FS as the lxc
source dir, when launching an application directly from the
host, by setting the glance image property lxc_root_source_dir.

glance image-update \
       --property lxc_init_path=/sbin/sh \
       --property lxc_root_source_dir=true \
       [image]

DocImapct
Partially implements blueprint libvirt-lxc-application-containers

Change-Id: I8c2deb83d1f12d2526e01f8cf37975637771b551

commit_message:
libvirt: don't mount an image if lxc source dir is provided

Currently, libvirt lxc driver is mounting an image to
an instance_dir/rootfs directory, is order to map it into the
container. However, there is no need to mount/umount the image,
in case of an application container case, when lxc_root_source_dir
is provided via the image properties.

DocImpact
Partially implements blueprint libvirt-lxc-application-containers
Change-Id: Ica44d2d499f1b5e5c5c89329b9f3a31bf00876d7

subject: Import and initialize oslo.messaging drivers for config options
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-11 21:11:49.000000000', 'files': ['autogenerate_config_docs/autohelp.py', 'autogenerate_config_docs/common.py'], 'message': "Import and initialize oslo.messaging drivers for config options

The config options for oslo.messaging drivers (rabbit_*, qpid_*, etc)
are not registered with oslo.config when any module is imported. You
have to instantiate an object of the appropriate driver for them to
be registered.

This means that modules that use oslo.messaging (glance, probably more
in the future) don't get those options listed in the docs. This commit
imports the drivers and instantiates them for known implementations,
in the least hacky way I can think of.

Change-Id: I931b2f39ab2b2c0de857b151865f1eaf77ba3162
"}]
commit_message:
Import and initialize oslo.messaging drivers for config options

The config options for oslo.messaging drivers (rabbit_*, qpid_*, etc)
are not registered with oslo.config when any module is imported. You
have to instantiate an object of the appropriate driver for them to
be registered.

This means that modules that use oslo.messaging (glance, probably more
in the future) don't get those options listed in the docs. This commit
imports the drivers and instantiates them for known implementations,
in the least hacky way I can think of.

Change-Id: I931b2f39ab2b2c0de857b151865f1eaf77ba3162

commit_message:
Update policy check for flavor related API

update policy check for v3 API, move from extension to core on flavor
manage. Also, add action policy check instead of check on flavor.
Remove policy check in db layer because the api layer already check
it in the policy check routine.

Added several test cases to do policy test for v2 and v3 flavor.

Change-Id: Ida904ff88cd2685986ab5559e89226b53aca59db
Implements: blueprint v3-api-policy

commit_message:
Update policy check on each action for agents

v3 api requested policy check on each action instead of the whole
topic, this patch update the check in agents and added some test
cases for policy check on agents.
Also, removed db layer admin policy check because it's already be
done at API layer.

commit_message:
Expose ML2 mechanism driver exceptions to the user

Previously, whenever a ML2 mechanism driver raised an exception, ie
in a precommit or postcommit method, that exception would be hidden
from the user because the _call_on_driver() method in managers.py
raises a generic MechanismDriverError exception.

This change is to change the message text of the MechanismDriverError
exception to also include the text from the last exception encountered
from the mechanism drivers.

Change-Id: Ib715f3d1303aebfb6d5c3f3f0580e8e8f004331b
Closes-Bug: #1273730

commit_message:
Use class attribute to represent 'project'

When sending a notification a resource_type is required, such as a
'project'. This value is consistent between the notification.created,
updated, delete, disabled methods in the Manager class, so use a class
attribute to represent it.

Change-Id: I65cc0ffb1d8811ae9f518492f998e426005345f0

commit_message:
raw_template hot parameter type data migration

Changes were made to the hot syntax which prevent invalid templates
already present in the database from being loaded as part of a stack
list. This database migration forces the parameter schema type to
be lowercase.

Change-Id: Iaa4b16e9b5188e6e99cda95e1c7fb0dc11c206f7
Partial-Bug: #1274288

subject: Ensures NetApp iSCSI driver correctly compares int values for size
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-18 22:50:42.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/netapp/iscsi.py'], 'message': 'Ensures NetApp iSCSI driver correctly compares int values for size

The NetApp iSCSI driver needs to verify that the new size requested
during an extend operation does not exceed the max_resize of the
lun.  However, the driver was doing a >= compare against str values
of the sizes rather than the int values.  This caused the incorrect
code path to be used in certain situations.

Change-Id: I8bc66c71db6b469c7adf00ce8b5091513fccb740
Closes-Bug: 1281279
'}]
commit_message:
Ensures NetApp iSCSI driver correctly compares int values for size

The NetApp iSCSI driver needs to verify that the new size requested
during an extend operation does not exceed the max_resize of the
lun.  However, the driver was doing a >= compare against str values
of the sizes rather than the int values.  This caused the incorrect
code path to be used in certain situations.

Change-Id: I8bc66c71db6b469c7adf00ce8b5091513fccb740
Closes-Bug: 1281279

This allows previewing a StackResource not as a single resource, but as
resources within a stack.  In order to do that, resources that inherit
from StackResource must override both ``child_template`` and
``child_params`` methods to allow the stack to be parsed.  If any of

'}]
commit_message:
Add StackResource specific preview behavior

This allows previewing a StackResource not as a single resource, but as
resources within a stack.  In order to do that, resources that inherit
from StackResource must override both ``child_template`` and
``child_params`` methods to allow the stack to be parsed.  If any of
these methods is missing, the preview will default to being just the
StackResource itself, and will be returned as a single resource.

Implements: blueprint preview-stack (partial)
Change-Id: I03be7e58a6809f5061546a469b69165d6ca70a30

commit_message:
Split large source file for Networking installation

One large source file contained Networking installation sections for
all nodes. This format disagreed with the structure of other chapters
and increased difficulty of maintenance tasks. In preparation for
rewriting the Networking chapter and restructuring associated portions
of the guide for Icehouse, I split this large file into smaller
files for configuring each node plus creating initial networks. Aside
from fixing some additional issues necessary to successfully build the
guide, this rather crude patch merely opens the door for additional
renovation and content patches.

Change-Id: I58645cd892de397e1bdef4914752e1b714655599
Closes-Bug: #1281347

commit_message:
Parameterize OPENSTACK_NEUTRON_NETWORK settings

Horizon can provide GUI support for Neutron's LBaaS, FWaaS, VPNaas,
and other services. However the settings to enable these is currently
hardcoded in the local_settings.py.erb template rather than being
parameterized, making it impossible for users to enable support for
these functions.  This patch adds a parameter hash to enable users to
select how they want to configure Neutron services and sets default
values to match the old hardcoded settings to maintain backward
compatibility.

Change-Id: Ibfa75a83a88d9bb26d65c026c7f913e000bce13f
Closes-Bug: #1274382

commit_message:
Add basic Python 3 tests

This uses `nose' to load and run tests for the time being, as
testrepository tries to load everything, which is not possible
currently. Until everything is Python 3 compatible, using `nose' will be
simpler to list the specific files we want to run.

Blueprint: make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: I4c8dbf11ac8c6e0f25bc60a3e880a30bf87a60bd

Check if MQ is rabbit before setting control_echange

is missing, so check existence of the attribute before using it.

subject: Allows for flexible NFS volume naming
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-18 21:05:12.000000000', 'files': ['recipes/volume.rb', 'templates/default/shares.conf.erb', 'attributes/default.rb', 'metadata.rb', 'README.md'], 'message': 'Allows for flexible NFS volume naming

It doesn't make sense to force all NFS exports to have the same
volume name, as you could be mounting from various different sources.
This change allows the user to specify the values for shares.conf
instead of having it rendered from "netapp_server_hostname:@export"

This is explicity for grizzly today, as I need it, but Blueprint is
submitted for allowing more generic NFS cinder in master.

Also adds rubocop as tests fail without it

Change-Id: Icd5c6d92a9ae8f5f68f8bb1ad62d180f388fde90
'}]
commit_message:
Allows for flexible NFS volume naming

It doesn't make sense to force all NFS exports to have the same
volume name, as you could be mounting from various different sources.
This change allows the user to specify the values for shares.conf
instead of having it rendered from "netapp_server_hostname:@export"

This is explicity for grizzly today, as I need it, but Blueprint is
submitted for allowing more generic NFS cinder in master.

Also adds rubocop as tests fail without it

Change-Id: Icd5c6d92a9ae8f5f68f8bb1ad62d180f388fde90

commit_message:
Adds Cloud Audit (CADF) Support for keystone authentication

This restores context passing to the manager layer which was originally
included to support auditing / logging (which we haven't supported until
now), and was later removed to support caching. However, we don't have
any reason to cache the results of authenticate() and it needs to be
audited. -dolphm

Change-Id: I2d43617f66fa2b23221dcfa4f7e935f64e458e1c
Implements: bp audit-event-record
DocImpact

commit_message:
VMware create_virtual_disk refactor

Several methods are repeating code for creating the virtual disk.
This refactor isolates the code for that task so it can be reused.

We mark the inner method as deprecated because we cannot remove

commit_message:
Cleanup node['cpu']['total'] work-around for fauxhai

The fauxhai fix for the cpu stanza has merged and is available in
fauxhai version 2.1.0 so reverting the workaround patch and ensuring
fauxhai 2.1.0 is used.

- Remove the node.set for ['cpu']['total'] in the spec tests

- Adjust the Gemfile.lock

commit_message:
Updates the version discovery by client

The Domain Quota Driver in Nova uses Keystone client to find
the list of projects in a domain. For this the V3 API is used.
But the keystone client always uses v2 and there is no v2 api
for listing projects in a domain. So code changed to use V3 when
nova asks the keystone to use V3.

Change-Id: I559df33c1654a62a5c3ba224c204761c013f49cf

commit_message:
Create an API endpoint for Zuul

This patch is the first part of the zuul-endpoint blueprint. It
creates the API endpoint in solum for triggers.

This endpoint has to be public, so this patch also add a wrapper
on keystone AuthProtocol to allow unauthenticated access to all
requests targeting an url starting with '/{api_version}/public/

Partially implements blueprint zuul-endpoint

commit_message:
Fix improper test for tunnel_types param

When VXLAN support was added to the ovs agent manifest, a new
parameter called tunnel_types was also added with the default
value being an empty array.  However, later in the code there's
an if loop that tests truth--and an empty array returns true.
This causes a line of the form:

tunnel_types =

to show up in /etc/neutron/plugins/openvswitch/ovs_neutron_plugin.ini
if the default value is used, which causes OVS to refuse to start.
This patch corrects the problem by properly testing the array.

Change-Id: I06ad6249ab7803676e49c026b4692f06ade269ed
Closes-Bug: #1281684
(cherry picked from commit f3a4b53a417db64ed7c26980893a4a8e3ccde83c)

commit_message:
Support setting a machine type to enable ARMv7/AArch64 guests to boot

By default the libvirt driver does not specify a machine type. On ARM systems
that results in a default type which will fail. This change provides two ways
to have Nova specify a machine type in the libvirt configuration:

1) The image can be tagged with the property "hw_machine_type=<type>"
2) If Nova detects an armv7 or aarch64 processor it will use vexpress-a15 or
   virt machine types respectively (this can be overridden with an image
   property)

Change-Id: I8aadfcf50e35a1370783ea795f80b29c1a71abff
Closes-Bug: #1261978
DocImpact

commit_message:
Fix compute_node_update() compatibility with older clients

A recent change changed the format of the data passed to conductor's
compute_node_update() method. The 'stats' element of 'values' was
changed from a dict to a JSON-encoded string. When older clients
call this method with a dict, the newer conductor puts the actual
dict in the SQL instead of a string, which breaks.

Change-Id: Ida1ad76752b1944f33c1aa9436ce36790705d6a5

commit_message:
InputScenarioUtils load images if glance available

The scenario_images utility of InputScenarioUtils shall
load the image list from glance only if glance is available.
Otherwise the test discovery process will fail if glance
is not available.

Closes bug 1277669

commit_message:
libvirt: support configurable wipe methods for LVM backed instances

Provide configurable methods to clear these volumes.
The new 'volume_clear' and 'volume_clear_size' options
are the same as currently supported by cinder.

* nova/virt/libvirt/imagebackend.py: Define the new options.
* nova/virt/libvirt/utils.py (clear_logical_volume): Support the
new options. Refactor the existing dd method out to
_zero_logic_volume().
* nova/tests/virt/libvirt/test_libvirt_utils.py: Add missing test cases
for the existing clear_logical_volume code, and for the new code
supporting the new clearing methods.
* etc/nova/nova.conf.sample: Add the 2 new config descriptions
to the [libvirt] section.

Change-Id: I5551197f9ec89ae2f9b051696bccdeb1af2c031f
Closes-Bug: #889299

commit_message:
Work around for httplib2 retries on timeout

httplib2 automatically retries a request on a timeout even if the request
is a POST. This can lead to orphaned objects being created that we
don't know about. This patch sets httplib2.RETRIES to 1 to avoid this.

Note: httplib2.RETRIES is only available in new versions of httplib2.
See: https://code.google.com/p/httplib2/issues/detail?id=124 for more
details.

Co-Authored-By: Ashwin Raveendran <ashw7n@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Sudheendra Murthy <sudhi.vm@gmail.com

Change-Id: I5648b644bb9df1fd2ea219159794d9d122696af0
Closes-bug: #1267649

commit_message:
Separate OVERCLOUD_DIB_EXTRA_ARGS into two new variables

OVERCLOUD_DIB_EXTRA_ARGS is separated out to
OVERCLOUD_CONTROL_DIB_EXTRA_ARGS and OVERCLOUD_COMPUTE_DIB_EXTRA_ARGS.

An element may not neccessarily want to be placed in both the
control and compute, so this is why we are making this distinction.

for accessing job binaries. Modify the JobBinary resource to
specify 'extra' as a filtered field.

commit_message:
Setting to use syslog in Murano added.

* Local logs added
* Logrotate configured
* Typos
* murano_use_syslog -> use_syslog
* murano_debug -> debug
* murano_verbose -> verbose
* syslog_log_facility
* murano user/group added back
* use bool values for debug/use_syslog

Replaces review https://review.openstack.org/#/c/62853/
Replaces review https://review.openstack.org/#/c/63705/

commit_message:
Add NIC bonding support in Nailgun

* Add a NodeBondInterface DB model.
* Add a new model rendering to the api/nodes/x/interfaces
  handler.
* Allow a bond creation via the handler.
* Add a data propagation to the deployment_serializer.
* Add Enum usage.
* Migration rules fixed.
* Tests fixed.
* Nets-to-NICs default assignment fixed.

TODO:
* New tests will be added soon.
* Add a lot of checks and validations.
* NodeNICCollectionhandler has an outdated behavior.
  Lets syncronize it with NodeNic handler.
* Bonding must be allowed to the nodes in cluster only.
* Bonding is not available in NovaNetwork.

Implements: blueprint nics-bonding-enabled-from-ui

Change-Id: Ib70bbe9fe897a07f2b7b201944333f70986bbb35

commit_message:
Fix wrong command to define neutron firewall class

The firewall_driver option in the OVS configuration file was not properly
defined for rpm based distributions: the key word was missing in the
openstack-config command, and the section name was incorrect.

Change-Id: I5346b3ddb39ae961437f0b675043130a8a5dcb5f
Closes-Bug: #1281177
backport: none

commit_message:
Minor refactor for syslog logging

- Fix missed log config notify for glance-api, glance-registry
- Fix confusing titles for generic/main Openstack services
- Removed unnecessary 'ensure absent' for config providers
- Removed confusing unused logging config for local logging cases
- Synced confusing 10-fuel & 20-fuel file lists to be the same
- Removed delaycompress option from logrotate configs
- Removed hardcoded logging_context_format_string,
  and logging_default_format_string config settings
- Removed clumsy value selectors for debug/verbose/use_syslog
- Use top scope for verbose, debug, use_syslog options in cluster*.pp

Implements blueprint: refactor-logging-puppet-openstack-services
CI retest4

Change-Id: I543c52c9fe6a95d3bc6eb6f87c0599e659ee01ec
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Use global to represent OS-TRUST:trust

When sending a notification a resource_type is required, such as a
'user', 'project', or 'OS-TRUST:trust'. This value is consistent between
operations so it can be stored in a class global variable.

commit_message:
doc(README): Have the user pass '-v' when starting marconi-server

Users sometimes get confused when maconi-server doesn't print out anything
about which IP and port it is listening on. Recommend passing '-v' so they
learn this trick right off the bat.

Change-Id: I49cd29566b18506fad4f9450ba46159f0a75590d

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-11 13:49:36.000000000', 'files': ['oslo/messaging/_executors/base.py'], 'message': 'Change log level for unexpected RPC exceptions

When an RPC server reports an exception that has not been
declared using expected_exceptions(), log it as a warning
instead of an error. These conditions are typically caused
by a lack of configuration in the server code, rather than
a real production deployment issue that needs an operator
to pay attention to the message.

We will revisit this decision in the next release, when
the LoggingStandards project moves from looking at error
level messages to warning messages.

Partial-bug: #1276163

Change-Id: I55503ddcf2e84566fdfc9d967d3babf4e1a61d7e
'}]
commit_message:
Change log level for unexpected RPC exceptions

When an RPC server reports an exception that has not been
declared using expected_exceptions(), log it as a warning
instead of an error. These conditions are typically caused
by a lack of configuration in the server code, rather than
a real production deployment issue that needs an operator
to pay attention to the message.

We will revisit this decision in the next release, when
the LoggingStandards project moves from looking at error
level messages to warning messages.

Partial-bug: #1276163

Change-Id: I55503ddcf2e84566fdfc9d967d3babf4e1a61d7e

commit_message:
Stop exporting in devtest_testenv

We don't need to export variables in testenv, they are going to be
written into the JSON file, and we don't source testenv in devtest.sh,
so they fall out of scope when the script finishes executing anyway.

Change-Id: Ife9571d42ecb389cff445422169d8480512490e6

commit_message:
Standardize config sample locations

All OpenStack projects store the full config sample in
etc/project_name/project_name.conf.sample, so we should do it in the same
manner.

Changes in etc/savanna:

* savanna.conf.sample -> savanna.conf.sample-basic
* savanna.conf.sample-full -> savanna.conf.sample

Additionally config sample was re-generated by config generator from
oslo that'll be added to Savanna in the next patch. Existing config
generation removed.

Change-Id: I7bfe1ab7cb32a9cdfe8f6b5ceead3dc97de74255

Removes the use of .cache/image-create/image-file-cache/{hash}

consistent with the other devtest scripts in that
images get cached in known locations in $TRIPLEO_ROOT.

commit_message:
Move ipmitool _set_boot_device to VendorPassthru

_set_boot_device must be exposed via vendor_passthru, allowing
operators to manually change it, and force to boot from net when
performing a pxe deploy.
Until now, it was just a private method of the power driver.

The cirros image can support the soft reboot, but we reboot the machine
before the acpid started, it leads to additional 120 second wait before

commit_message:
Let the soft reboot really happen in the minimum scenario

The cirros image can support the soft reboot, but we reboot the machine
before the acpid started, it leads to additional 120 second wait before
nova falls back to the hard reboot.
As a solution we will ssh the machine before reboot, because the ssh
server starts after the acpid, so we will send the ACPI event, only
when the acpid is really running.

Change-Id: I3700a374dc937086518c5c843a288e935ab458bf

commit_message:
libvirt: making set_host_enabled to be a private methods

Currently _set_host_enabled() is being used only for internal libvirt
driver purposes, which doesn't correlate to set_host_enabled in the
compute API.

_set_host_enabled in the driver is disabling and re-enabling
the compute service automatically and shouldn't be exposed to the users.

Also, adding disable_reason as an optional variable and enabled variable
to be boolean only.

Change-Id: I5fd13ef352fcbb4a1c96764a9e473cdaf7b128da
Closes-Bug: #1251803

commit_message:
Add support for creating heat stack domain

The Heat instance-users blueprint requires an additional domain
where heat creates projects and users related to stack resources
so add support for creating this domain when configured to install
Heat.  Note a workaround is currently required to make the
openstack command work with the v3 keystone API.

Change-Id: I36157372d85b577952b55481ca5cc42146011a54

subject: Remove the libvirtError log in compute agent
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-18 04:10:03.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometer/compute/pollsters/disk.py', 'ceilometer/compute/pollsters/net.py'], 'message': 'Remove the libvirtError log in compute agent

When instance is stopped or suspend, compute agent will raise libvirtError,
but this is an expected error, and we have handled the expection in this bugfix:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/ceilometer/+bug/1209509.

In the above bugfix, it logs both error and warning log, but the error log is
really confused to people, because the compute agent is running normally, so
I think we should remove the error log, and the remaining warning log is enough.

Fixes: bug 1281396
Change-Id: Ie8e3e17992f8f70cd57cad50432858314e73a1a2
'}]
commit_message:
Remove the libvirtError log in compute agent

When instance is stopped or suspend, compute agent will raise libvirtError,
but this is an expected error, and we have handled the expection in this bugfix:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/ceilometer/+bug/1209509.

In the above bugfix, it logs both error and warning log, but the error log is
really confused to people, because the compute agent is running normally, so
I think we should remove the error log, and the remaining warning log is enough.

Fixes: bug 1281396
Change-Id: Ie8e3e17992f8f70cd57cad50432858314e73a1a2

commit_message:
REST method to fetch deployments metadata for a server

This REST method returns a grouped collection of deployment resource
metadata which a server uses as its configuration inputs.

Previously the index method was overloaded to perform this function too.

Currently this will be called by heat-engine when the server
resource metadata is polled, but it should eventually be possible
for servers to call this method directly so that a stack does not
need to be parsed every time a server polls for metadata.

partial blueprint hot-software-config

Change-Id: Ie81e413459eaf7a24658be84152d88228f42c6b6

commit_message:
Allow log disable in account/container server

Logging can be disabled in the object server, but not in the
account and container server though both sample configs already
include that setting. This patch allows to disable logging for
account and container server as well.

Functionality is ensured by some additional tests.

Closes-Bug: 1280954

commit_message:
Make POST/PUT redirects use original methods

Commands like 'stack-update' and 'action-suspend' use PUT or
POST methods when interacting with the Heat API. They also
require the use of redirects. Currently redirects for these use
GET instead of the original method which leads to undesired
outcomes. This commit ensures that the redirect always uses the
original method.

Change-Id: Iee578ea23c842e48f2d73992804f9c2efb9c7f43
Closes-bug: #1280158

subject: Calculate dependencies based on unresolved template
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-17 22:06:02.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/resource.py'], 'message': 'Calculate dependencies based on unresolved template

We previously calculated dependencies based on the template snippet for the
resource after static functions had been resolved. The distinction between
static and runtime resolution of data is going away soon, which causes
problems with that. Rather than rewriting the dependency code now, just
calculate the dependencies from the unresolved template instead. A future
patch will replace this code by allowing the functions themselves to
calculate their dependencies.

Change-Id: I2d193025219ce78b811090fc4eb459a89bd2fa26
'}]
commit_message:
Calculate dependencies based on unresolved template

We previously calculated dependencies based on the template snippet for the
resource after static functions had been resolved. The distinction between
static and runtime resolution of data is going away soon, which causes
problems with that. Rather than rewriting the dependency code now, just
calculate the dependencies from the unresolved template instead. A future
patch will replace this code by allowing the functions themselves to
calculate their dependencies.

Change-Id: I2d193025219ce78b811090fc4eb459a89bd2fa26

commit_message:
Add a base class for pluggable functions

These functions can be substituted for their corresponding syntax in the
parse tree and lazily evaluated at the time their output is needed. Thus,
no distinction between statically-resolvable and runtime-resolvable
functions is required.

Change-Id: I3e89b6ee0d17b6755b35ab52b52a22a8d3db6c29

commit_message:
Prevent user introspection of Python objects

The get_attr and get_param built-in functions in HOT allowed introspection
of Python objects as well as traversing lists and maps, which we very much
do not want.

Fixes bug #1280526

Change-Id: I5f8f4bfa37d33eb0a1df962b69a3b6e029ad0048

commit_message:
Don't reply to notification message

The notification listener doesn't have anything to send to the notifier
and the notifier doesn't attend to receive something.

So this patch remove the message reply when the listener is a
notification
listener.

Partial implements blueprint notification-subscriber-server

Change-Id: Ic989947ba3b6894cde788422842fca19159ea261

subject: Make wrap_db_error() a class decorator
revisions:
[{'number': 13, 'created': '2014-02-13 09:54:59.000000000', 'files': ['tests/unit/db/sqlalchemy/test_sqlalchemy.py', 'openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py'], 'message': "Make wrap_db_error() a class decorator

For a long time _wrap_db_error() had been a function decorator, which
used the global Engine instance to find out the DB backend name.

We don't have the global Engine instance now, so wrap_db_error() must
be able to access Session instance context instead. And it is meant
to be applied to Session methods only. Which means we can reasonably
assume, that the wrapper function always receives 'self' argument
pointing to a Session subclass instance. Though, it's obviously would
be better, if we could enforce that wrap_db_error() was applied only
to Session subclasses methods at the decorator application time
rather than at the runtime.

In Python 3 there is no way to distinguish between an 'unbound' class
method and a general function (as there are no unbound methods
anymore). So the cleaner solution must be making wrap_db_error()
a class decorator instead, which will raise TypeError when applied
to not a Session subclass.

Related-Bug: #1263908

Co-authored-by: Victor Sergeyev <vsergeyev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ib3f5979c4e6e2ab98803eea9107cfe4c93bd2884
"}]
commit_message:
Make wrap_db_error() a class decorator

For a long time _wrap_db_error() had been a function decorator, which
used the global Engine instance to find out the DB backend name.

We don't have the global Engine instance now, so wrap_db_error() must
be able to access Session instance context instead. And it is meant
to be applied to Session methods only. Which means we can reasonably
assume, that the wrapper function always receives 'self' argument
pointing to a Session subclass instance. Though, it's obviously would
be better, if we could enforce that wrap_db_error() was applied only
to Session subclasses methods at the decorator application time
rather than at the runtime.

In Python 3 there is no way to distinguish between an 'unbound' class
method and a general function (as there are no unbound methods
anymore). So the cleaner solution must be making wrap_db_error()
a class decorator instead, which will raise TypeError when applied
to not a Session subclass.

Related-Bug: #1263908

Co-authored-by: Victor Sergeyev <vsergeyev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ib3f5979c4e6e2ab98803eea9107cfe4c93bd2884

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

commit_message:
Make v2 and v3 identity apis configurable

This commit adds a config option to the identity feature enabled group
to specify whether the v2 and/or v3 apis are enabled in keystone. In
the process of adding this feature the logical split between v2 and v3
tests in the identity api tests is made more clear. Additionally as part,
of the split several bugs are fixed where the v2 api was being called
in the v3 tests.

Change-Id: I0d727f3567c82fe512b956110bb813119ced0b3d

revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2014-02-12 08:32:09.000000000', 'files': ['templates/default/ceph.client.keyring.erb', 'templates/default/ceph.conf.erb', 'spec/ceph_spec.rb', 'recipes/ceph_client.rb', 'attributes/default.rb'], 'message': 'Add ceph_client recipe

To use RBD as a block-storage backend, both the compute workers and the
cinder-api service need to be able to talk to the Ceph cluster.

Nova-compute makes use of the `rbd` CLI tool, cinder-api and libvirt use
librbd's Python binding.  Therefore, it might make sense to have this
"common" recipe provide the necessary infrastructure to a) reach the
ceph cluster and b) install ceph packages if need be.

Besides block storage, RBD can also be used for storing images, so
that's another reason to put this into openstack-common.

This commit also introduces a template, "ceph.client.keyring.erb", to
allow the creation of client keys from other recipes in a DRY way:

    template '/etc/ceph/client.cinder.keyring' do
      template 'ceph.client.keyring.erb'
      cookbook 'openstack-common'
      owner node['openstack']['block-storage']['user']
      group node['openstack']['block-storage']['group']
      mode '600'
      variables(
        name: rbd_user,
        key: rbd_key
      )
    end

A LWRP for this would be an improvement, but this should do for now.

Implements: blueprint rbd-for-block-storage

Change-Id: Icd046830c9542bd71fa3a1857c1f4d1bb3c41cec
'}]
commit_message:
Add ceph_client recipe

To use RBD as a block-storage backend, both the compute workers and the
cinder-api service need to be able to talk to the Ceph cluster.

Nova-compute makes use of the `rbd` CLI tool, cinder-api and libvirt use
librbd's Python binding.  Therefore, it might make sense to have this
"common" recipe provide the necessary infrastructure to a) reach the
ceph cluster and b) install ceph packages if need be.

Besides block storage, RBD can also be used for storing images, so
that's another reason to put this into openstack-common.

This commit also introduces a template, "ceph.client.keyring.erb", to
allow the creation of client keys from other recipes in a DRY way:

    template '/etc/ceph/client.cinder.keyring' do
      template 'ceph.client.keyring.erb'
      cookbook 'openstack-common'
      owner node['openstack']['block-storage']['user']
      group node['openstack']['block-storage']['group']
      mode '600'
      variables(
        name: rbd_user,
        key: rbd_key
      )
    end

A LWRP for this would be an improvement, but this should do for now.

Implements: blueprint rbd-for-block-storage

Change-Id: Icd046830c9542bd71fa3a1857c1f4d1bb3c41cec

commit_message:
Clear date picker fields every time 'Other' Period is selected

In subsequent selections of 'Other' from Period field in Admin > Resources
Usage Overview panel previously picked dates for From and To fields remain.
This patch is to clear those fields every time 'Other' is selected, as
preserving the values could be confusing.

Change-Id: If82aa26cd453a038fb8821a4c33f979dd4dbb8a9
Closes-Bug: #1280441

commit_message:
Fix doubly registered rpc_backend option

common/servce.py was importing openstack/common/rpc.  This directory
was removed, but if .pyc files were left in the directory (as is the
case with devstack), nova would fail to start.  This is an update of
service.py from oslo-incubator which corrects the problem.

Change-Id: I5be3f5e01541eaaf9c44c7d80fbc38ccb536dd68
Closes-Bug: #1275967

Support building wheels (PEP-427)

these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Support building wheels (PEP-427)

these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

commit_message:
VPNaaS API Tests Enhancements

Added the following tests:
 - test_admin_create_vpn_service_for_tenant:
   Admin user creates VPN Service for tenant.

 - test_admin_create_ike_policy_for_tenant:
   Admin user creates IKE Policy for tenant.

 - test_list_ipsec_policies:
   List API test for ipsecpolicy resources.

 - test_create_update_delete_ipsec_policy:
   Create, Update and Delete API tests for ipsecpolicy resources.

 - test_show_ipsec_policy:
   Show API test for ipsecpolicy resources.

Extended the following tests:
 - test_show_vpn_service:
   Now tests to check whether the returned status has a
   valid value.

 - test_create_update_delete_ike_policy:
   Now also updates encryption_algorithm, ike_version,
   and lifetime in update tests. Verifies whether test was
   successful by comparing with vpn_service object returned by
   show API call.
   Also now checks whether delete was succesful by asserting
   that is the ikepolicy is no longer returned by list_ikepolicies.

Minor edits to base.py and network_client_base.py to support
ipsecpolicy resources.

Change-Id: I0f2f932f01d9d370c46572c532092566402d656b

subject: Automatic retry db.api query if db connection lost
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 1561, 'name': 'Russell Bryant', 'email': 'rbryant@redhat.com', 'username': 'russellb'}, {'_account_id': 1849, 'name': 'Joe Gordon', 'email': 'joe.gordon0@gmail.com', 'username': 'jogo'}, {'_account_id': 2166, 'name': 'SmokeStack CI', 'username': 'smokestack', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 7491, 'name': 'Viktor Serhieiev', 'email': 'viktor.sergeyev@gmail.com', 'username': 'vsergeyev'}, {'_account_id': 9578, 'name': 'DB Datasets CI', 'email': 'turbo-hipster@lists.rcbops.com', 'username': 'turbo-hipster', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-02-10 16:39:50.000000000', 'files': ['etc/nova/nova.conf.sample', 'nova/openstack/common/db/api.py', 'nova/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py'], 'message': "Automatic retry db.api query if db connection lost

This synk changes from Oslo patch  Ifd848ea70a62fb9f7ccbc8bfd22a10ab9d3135c9

Patch allows to retry db.api method call if db connection was lost temporally.
It can be done in a such way:
 - We should use annotate all methods which are safe to retry with
   @safe_for_db_retry, if it's totally safe to retry these functions
 - And we must allow db-retry feature in config (`use_db_reconnect` option
   in a `database` group). It's will allow db-retry for all db.api methods.

If function suppose to be retried and it's got `db-gone-away` error,
it's will calls in a loop until it succeeds, or until maximum retries
count will be reached.
Maximum retries count and timeout between retries attempts are configurable.

We use SQLA engine.dialect.is_disconnect() function to determine
broken db connection so it's should work for all supported SQLA
backends (MySQL, PostgreSQL, DB2 and SQLite supported as well).

Added wrapper for session and query methods. This wrapper catch
exceptions caused by broken db connection and re-raise it as
DBConnectionError exception.

Note, that it's safely to use db-retry feature only if all db.api
queries use single transaction.

At the moment this feature is experimental, so disabled by default.

Previous attempt was https://review.openstack.org/#/c/10797/

Implements: blueprint db-reconnect

Co-authored-by: Devananda van der Veen <devananda.vdv@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ic57a4dbdf52922730cf2de89606ec1f8f2e629f9
"}]
commit_message:
Automatic retry db.api query if db connection lost

This synk changes from Oslo patch  Ifd848ea70a62fb9f7ccbc8bfd22a10ab9d3135c9

Patch allows to retry db.api method call if db connection was lost temporally.
It can be done in a such way:
 - We should use annotate all methods which are safe to retry with
   @safe_for_db_retry, if it's totally safe to retry these functions
 - And we must allow db-retry feature in config (`use_db_reconnect` option
   in a `database` group). It's will allow db-retry for all db.api methods.

If function suppose to be retried and it's got `db-gone-away` error,
it's will calls in a loop until it succeeds, or until maximum retries
count will be reached.
Maximum retries count and timeout between retries attempts are configurable.

We use SQLA engine.dialect.is_disconnect() function to determine
broken db connection so it's should work for all supported SQLA
backends (MySQL, PostgreSQL, DB2 and SQLite supported as well).

Added wrapper for session and query methods. This wrapper catch
exceptions caused by broken db connection and re-raise it as
DBConnectionError exception.

Note, that it's safely to use db-retry feature only if all db.api
queries use single transaction.

At the moment this feature is experimental, so disabled by default.

Previous attempt was https://review.openstack.org/#/c/10797/

Implements: blueprint db-reconnect

Co-authored-by: Devananda van der Veen <devananda.vdv@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ic57a4dbdf52922730cf2de89606ec1f8f2e629f9

Port, which is used to calculate EC2 request signature on client side
was not included into parameters used for signature verification.
This resulted in authentication error for clients who used port
to calculate Signature. Now port is included and support for clients
who do not use it is still retained.

Closes-Bug: 1278526

commit_message:
Adds port to parameters used for EC2 signature verification

Port, which is used to calculate EC2 request signature on client side
was not included into parameters used for signature verification.
This resulted in authentication error for clients who used port
to calculate Signature. Now port is included and support for clients
who do not use it is still retained.
ec2_port option has been moved from nova.api.ec2.cloud to nova.api.ec2

Change-Id: Icb8d8b4b3006f94773a88c68e94ebbd2a9a28e33
Closes-Bug: 1278526

commit_message:
Configure plugins by name

To configure core plugin or service plugins, instead of using class
names, simpler names can also be used.

Example:
service_plugins = router, firewall, lbaas
core_plugins = linuxbridge

It is a new feature brought in Icehouse (thanks to stevedor): http://git.io/QfyiLw
Bringing it into puppet-neutron simplifies the parameters use for end-user.

Change-Id: Ib96cc8ea67e89c37226ee6b9d1ae811fa1507672
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Deprecate bind_host parameter

Since Icehouse release, bind_host parameter has been deprecated for two
new flags: public_bind_host and admin_bind_host: http://git.io/RGao7w

This patch deprecates bind_host param and ensure backward compatibility
and configure Keystone using the two new flags.

Closes-bug: #1271269

Change-Id: I60db96fc99311280ae5051e1d9cfb5d46b3374a2
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Adding manage_service parameter to all services

When set to false, enables puppet to configure a service without
starting/stopping it on each run.  This may be necessary when
using an external clustering system (Corosync/Pacemaker, for
example).  Defaults to true.

Change-Id: Iff21ee384fa857e1ddec0e15ca85df8aedad3e80

commit_message:
Replace notifier with oslo.messaging

Oslo messaging works slightly differently in that you create a Notifier
object once which contains config such as publisher_id and then you
re-use that object when issuing messages.

DocImpact: The options for setting up RPC and notifications have changed
to reflect oslo.messaging.

Blueprint: oslo-messaging
Change-Id: I2d08fb405e68df37866b3799ab7339ebd9894f05

commit_message:
Libvirt:Instance resize confirm issue against NFS

when I test resize-confirm on NFS (KVM) using at least two
compute nodes, OSError will occur when try to cleanup the
backup instance directory and will make instance status
"Error".

One way to cleanup resize is using delay_on_retry and
maximum attempts setting. Replace rmtree() because
execute() have more parameters choices.

Closes-Bug: #1248019

(cherry picked from commit Ifb9a500bbba805af0317307c2e7d6903dcd02ad1)
Change-Id: I341adaca7e9d7f6adba0c09af6db2538f7e8bba8

commit_message:
Don't disable SELinux in cloud-init's boothook.sh

This is a first step towards fixing #1257410 as outlined in the bug
report.

Disabling SELinux is not necessary, but the fact that we're using both
the `user` directive in cloudinit/config and `useradd` in boothook.sh
is a bit confusing so this documents the reasons for both.

Change-Id: Ife4fec99650341de698eb51741d96f95de00dcf0
Partial-Bug: #1257410

commit_message:
Add support for backing up volume metadata

This commit adds a new versioned api to the backup driver base
class which all backup driver implementations should use in order
to support backing up volume metadata as well as data. The general
rule here is that we backup all metadata from a set of db tables
and can then be selective about what we restore.

As part of this commit, Ceph backup driver implements the new api
to backup volume metadata (including glance metadata) thus
supporting restoring volumes as bootable.

It is expected that the other backup driver implementations will
follow suit and adopt this approach.

Implements: blueprint cinder-backup-volume-metadata-support
Fixes: bug 1137908
Change-Id: Icf2f1202d827d2435e09f5dad0f6f022f35dceee

commit_message:
Remove vi modelines

We don't need to have the vi modelines in each source file,
it can be set in a user's vimrc if required.
Also a check is added to hacking to detect if they are re-added.

Change-Id: Ia98a2fbc3f1ae7a156ccbe65b28ce899a31f0378
Closes-Bug: #1229324

commit_message:
Replace Midonet port groups with IP address groups

Replacing port groups with IP address groups. With Neutron security
groups implemented as Midonet port groups, we were unable to support
security rules with security group as a criterion because we didn't
know the destination port at the time of egress to the network. This
change implements neutron security groups as Midonet IP address
groups. This allows us to perform the security group check because the
destination IP address is known at all times.

Change-Id: Ia60ba8edf94406520b36ef4e465574b6e5fb3c0d
Closes-Bug: #1244025

commit_message:
Fixes security rules in Midonet plugin

Fixes several issues with the rule chains in Midonet plugins, including
adding a rule to drop egress traffic by default, adding security group
support to a port's egress chain, and correctly adding/deleting jump
rules from port chains when changing a port's security groups. Also
fixes several pep8 issues.

Change-Id: Ib80bd22135b220b0e8113556ac7a2b2d9261c954
Closes-Bug: #1231790

commit_message:
Deleted duplicated method in cliutils.

Method import_class in cliutils duplicates method in importutils module,
and method import_versioned_module is more related to import tools,
so it is moved in appropriate module.

bp common-client-library-2

commit_message:
Add API support for stack preview

Add endpoint for previewing a stack as returned by the engine.  The call
is similar to a create_stack call and takes the same parameters, but
will issue a preview instead of a create.  The response will be the
formatted stack plus the formatted resources that would exist with that
template/parameters.

Implements: blueprint preview-stack (partial)
Change-Id: I5fcfa76e741c556a7edf222805b41923344becbe

commit_message:
Native Nova Server compatibility for Cloud Server

Make the Rackspace Cloud Server resource compatible with the native
Nova Server resource so that a template author can replace
OS::Nova::Server with Rackspace::Cloud::Server, without making any other
changes, to make the resource use Rackspace Cloud Servers instead of
Nova.

Blueprint native-nova-cloud-server
Change-Id: I312ddc25e02843b0116b8a2cb88defef05ca88ac

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2014-02-11 09:14:26.000000000', 'files': ['bin/swift'], 'message': 'Add option to skip downloading/uploading identical files

swift has already the upload option "--changed" to upload only changed
files. This patch adds a similar feature by comparing the md5 of the
local file to the remote object etag.

When used in combination with download the MD5 hexdigest of each file
is sent with an "If-None-Match" header to skip downloading identical files.

When used in combination with upload the MD5 is compared to the remote
etag by using the already existing HEAD request.

Change-Id: I727b0456558c6a7742b2428c6d1c45c4bfaf66e9
'}]
commit_message:
Add option to skip downloading/uploading identical files

swift has already the upload option "--changed" to upload only changed
files. This patch adds a similar feature by comparing the md5 of the
local file to the remote object etag.

When used in combination with download the MD5 hexdigest of each file
is sent with an "If-None-Match" header to skip downloading identical files.

When used in combination with upload the MD5 is compared to the remote
etag by using the already existing HEAD request.

Change-Id: I727b0456558c6a7742b2428c6d1c45c4bfaf66e9

commit_message:
Fix how migration's cli register db connection opt

It's not good to duplicate the same oslo.config options in one project
due to the fact that it'll be hadled incorrectly by different config
sample generation tools. The better option is to use CONF.import_opt
that will import oslo/db/sqla/session that already registers db connection
option with good description and backward compatibility support.

Change-Id: I71c4c0442464f2b4e88fb172f5d5e23daa133834

commit_message:
Use assertIsNone or assertIsNotNone in tests

Replace assertEqual(None, *) or assertTrue(A is None) or
assertTrue(A is not None) with assertIsNone or assertIsNotNone
in tests to have more clear messages in case of failure.

Change-Id: I6067e384723c3de3c6c59281903a44b79157fb83

Handle COPY verb in container quota middleware

The patch fix the ability to bypass the account
quota using the COPY verb. The quotas for destination
container are now checked before the copy.

commit_message:
feat(sql/driver): expose ControlDriver, more config

This patch adds two features to our current sqlalchemy driver:

- option to configure connection URI for driver
- Skeleton of ControlDriver written

With the ControlDriver, the expected methods were stubbed out.

Small fix: all controller methods not yet implemented now raise
NotImplementedError.

Change-Id: I1cd4a4d75cbbee7f0ff574c5be4d11660359ab7e
Partially-Implements: blueprint: sql-storage-driver

commit_message:
Shorten swift-internal:// to swift://

The internal/external distinction can be handled with meta-data
instead of encoding it within the url. So we can simply start using
swift://.

This patch keeps the swift-internal:// option around until we decide
it can simply be removed.

Change-Id: I5ea3d93319daf426539abc78ae826b6594035df9
Implements: blueprint swift-url-proto-cleanup

commit_message:
Raise the default max header to accommodate large tokens

PKI tokens hit the default limit if there is enough
services defined in the keystone catalog.

Also the v3 catalog is larger than the v2 catalog which would explain
why this bug is being hit just now.

This change adds the configuration option max_header_line to each of the
API confurations which has a default of 16384.

Closes-Bug: #1190149
Change-Id: I5da09aa08a1242c5e356bd8bf532baa9347ce075

commit_message:
Add JSONEncodedType with enforced type checking

Add abstract base class for JSONEncoded properties which: 1. Does type
checking to make sure we're serializing what we really expect
2. Ensures that default value of the field matches default value of
that type, so we have consistent interface. This patch creates two child
classes JSONEncodedDict and JSONEncodedList and updates SA models
correspondingly.

Change-Id: I528ac64e998e9a874feb16709d7617feb4b09c8a
Closes-Bug: #1270146

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-17 20:50:36.000000000', 'files': ['test/functionalnosetests/swift_testing.py'], 'message': 'Move location of HTTPException in swift_testing

While doing some work around swiftclient Python 3 support, httplib
imports were changed to use six.moves in order to access httplib in Py2
and http.client in Py3. Tests related to those changes are failing
because these functional tests are depending on HTTPException being

	test/functionalnosetests/swift_testing.py

commit_message:
Move location of HTTPException in swift_testing

While doing some work around swiftclient Python 3 support, httplib
imports were changed to use six.moves in order to access httplib in Py2
and http.client in Py3. Tests related to those changes are failing
because these functional tests are depending on HTTPException being
a name in swiftclient.client. These tests should acces that name from
its canonical location in httplib (or, eventually, a Py3 friendly
location like six.moves).

Conflicts:
	test/functionalnosetests/swift_testing.py

Change-Id: I6335d465574045daedab47e5fe23c415d171a83a
(cherry picked from commit 180cd18da64b59c39ec1696e4316b18711d1fb82)
